column5: We have our tickets,again 65 tagged perch or so. Daily prizes. Have not been for 10 years. Anyone know where a free/reasonable place now to unload your boat and park?.Really looking forward to it.
There is a free launch across from tudhope park off 12 south.  I haven’t used it in a few years but that’s always where I put in to fish that area.

All depends on the weather.  No more sitting in a winter suit, gave that up.  The last couple of years it's not been all that great.  I'll try it once or twice, if there's no fish then there's other things to do.
Have not been in years. Especially with so much shoreline in the area being posted.
That reminds me, never did hear much about the Barrie fall perch festival either last fall.
Never did see the 100 boats near centennial beach last fall either. Unloaded there before in Orillia ,kinda remembered parking across the street ,maybe a early morning road trip.
